column4: the switch to prompt has been fantastic for my team and i. prompt's software has enabled us to deliver much better patient care. the telehealth integration has been seamless and hugely valuable for us during these trying times. the prompt team has been responsive and we are able to pivot and correct errors in a timely manner which will improve our cash flow and reimbursement now and going forward. i highly recommend prompt.

column4: we demoed several systems and after test driving reli’s system i was sold. it’s easy to learn and use without useless features, bright colors which make the screen noisy, crowded and harsh on the eyes. from scheduling patients, utilizing the emr, insurance processing to balance billing the relimed system has increased my efficency which allows me to do other tasks. customer service is awesome…… the support team actually answers the phone without prompts and transfering me to another department with long hold times. issues for the most part are resolved with one call and if not the team does follow up.

column4: i took on a new office and this software from another billing service. one hour of quick training from the previous biller and i was on my own. i was so impressed with how easily i was able to navigate thru and learn the software on my own. very user-friendly and the support team is amazing. i was able to email any questions and they responded within 24 hours w easy to understand answers. i also called and someone was always available to help me right away. easy to learn and amazing support staff. i highly recommend this software.

column4: there are many good qualities of this system. i have worked in the healthcare field for 12 years now and i am over 5 primary care practices currently. i have always kept up with different systems such as allscripts, athena, and epic. the systems do much of the same but once you sign a contract with the larger systems the customer service goes down and changes to the larger systems are impossible it seems. i first look at cost; reli med is way more affordable compared to the other systems. second, i look at how easy it is to use. reli med is very user-friendly from the front desk to the providers. reli med is constantly improving the system to customize for the providers; which is a great plus. other systems will point you to a video online and do not explain it like reli med.

column4: relimed emr is very user friendly. we felt that the learning curve was very small because the screens are so straightforward. we can easily access our patients’ information and communicate with our staff. most importantly, we were able to make our transition easy to reli med from a different emr that our practice used. we noticed improvements in efficiency from the start. their team is always open to suggestions, listens to our needs, and addresses those needs.

column4: we love the flexibility of this emr system and the support that’s available when we need it. we guarantee you’ll actually reach a support team member when you call relimed’s office. there’s no runaround and transfers from operators. real, live relimed team members are always available for support when we call! this is truly helpful when we are in need of quick answers to our problems and want them resolved immediately, which was difficult with our previous emr service provider. relimed has gone above and beyond to make the transition from the other system smooth; they helped us pull the necessary data from the old system when the previous vendor did not respond to any of our communication.

column4: my staff and i are very pleased with how easy relimed makes everything from scheduling to charting for a psychiatric practice. we feel very comfortable using the system due to its simplicity and user-friendliness, yet we are always impressed with how technologically advanced the system is beneath the surface. with relimed emr, we can enter the 5 axes of diagnosis easily. goal tracking is really simple too.

column4: training for the system was phenomenal, and the implementation staff worked with us in incorporating our templates into the system. we have also found that the support team is constantly available if we do have a question; we are always able to reach someone on the phone immediately instead of being put on hold or having to deal with an answering machine. the support staff members are knowledgeable, friendly, and polite, and the always take the time to fix the problem or help us understand what we missed.

column4: our pediatric practice has been using relimed emr for almost a year now, and we have found it to be simple to use and well suited for a pediatric clinic. having seen other systems, i think it’s by far a top notch emr for pediatric providers. i have been pleased with the system’s ease of use and the attentiveness of the company’s support staff. reli med support team members are truly dedicated in making you happy. they actively listen to your support calls and work to promptly meet your needs.

column4: reli med solutions provides an emr that allows your practice to document patient encounters efficiently and thoroughly. their system offers comprehensive age and gender specific charting templates, and the great thing is that the reli med developers will work with your practice to customize the templates to your liking. if you are looking for a system that is particularly pediatric friendly, relimed emr will definitely fulfill your needs.

column4: i have been using relimed emr since 2010. in december 2012, i started using reli med’s billing services too. their billing services team does an excellent job with my clinic’s revenue cycle management. i would highly recommend that every practice using relimed emr/pm begin using their billing services.

column4: before choosing relimed, we were signed on with a “highly rated” emr (which shall remain nameless). the product was pretty good – not as easy and intuitive as relimed – but fairly good. however, once we signed on – they disappeared. on numerous occasions we had questions, or ran into problems, and tried to contact them. they never answered the phone! i ended up having to call their “corporate headquarters” in san francisco to get someone from their southern u.s. (main) office to call me back. spent two hours on the phone just trying to speak with a live person!

column4: since we’ve begun using it in the office, we’ve had to contact relimed’s technical department to ask a question. i think you’d find this to be true with any emr you choose. what differentiates relimed emr from others is you can actually reach a live person all of the time. yesterday, july 4th – a holiday – we called in for a question and the call was picked up on the second ring. the technician was extremely knowledgable and friendly. she spent about 20 minutes on the phone with the three of us. the “problem” wasn’t a problem with the emr, but was on our end – as we hadn’t used this particular function before. the tech assumed control of our computer – with our permission – and walked us through the operation, which ended up being very easy. we’ve experienced this same level of personal service on two other occasions before this.

column4: i am a physician in raleigh, north carolina, and i have been using relimed emr since july of 2012. i have been very pleased with the flexibility of the system, and the development team’s willingness to set up/alter charting templates to best fit my workflow. the reli med solutions support staff is very responsive when i call for assistance. i appreciate reaching a live customer support rep when i call their office.

column4: reli med solutions also provided assistance as i began attesting to the ehr incentive program. using their system, i was able to meet all of the requirements necessary to receive the meaningful use incentive payments. because of the excellent support and affordability, i would recommend reli med solutions to any practice seeking an ehr system.

column4: in the fall of 2012, following six plus months of looking at several vendor solutions for emr/ehr, we chose relimed emr. we went live in october 2012 and migrated from paper to electronic charts. by spring of 2013, we implemented their fully integrated solution, namely both the electronic medical records (emr) and practice management (billing).

column4: as the providers (md’s and np’s) and the support staff (nurses, cna’s and receptionists) learned the system, it became obvious that a good choice had been made. the relimed emr/pm solution design represents a very well thought out system. coupled with a high level of adaptability and ease of customization, we can confidently endorse it as being one of the best, and may be the best, in the market place. it is apparent that a vast amount of high level thinking has gone into system design and architecture, even before beginning to write a single piece of code.

column4: furthermore, once installed, the quality of support has been phenomenal. regardless of what question is being asked, relimed staff has handled the same in the most professional manner. help is made available, whatever it takes. there have been times, when either a new feature has been requested or an issue has been reported. the response has always been a very swift and cooperative one. flaws, however rare, are addressed with a sense of urgency and the new feature(s) incorporated in a timely manner.

column4: i manage an internal medicine practice in north carolina and we have used reli med emr since 2011. i would recommend this emr to any practice that wants something customizable and simple to learn. as an office administrator, i can create new templates and alter old templates quickly and easily. and if i ever run into any questions, i know i can count on a member of the reli med support team to answer my calls.

column4: as an office manager at a pediatric practice, i find reli to be very easy to use and the customer support is always available with no hold times! the scheduling is similar to our previous software, but there are some differences that have helped in time management, organization and communication. no more time is wasted on pulling charts and sorting through countless printed information to find what i need.

column4: reli med solutions has a great staff that is very helpful and courteous. they take your thoughts and ideas and they make them functional within their system. their sytem is very user friendly. their team is full of ideas on how to improve the working of their system and they listen when the client talks about how they would like things to work. lisa and clint and renu are very knowledgeable about the working of the medical system, emr and billing. you will not be disappointed in this system.

column4: Healthcare providers must balance patient care with administrative work, and without the right tools, filling out tedious paperwork can take vital time away from patients. Switching to an RXNT software solution can help you complete administrative tasks more efficiently and accurately. With our affordable, cloud-based healthcare software, you and your staff can spend more time doing what you do best—delivering patient care.

column4:
Kareo was built with the biller’s daily workflow in mind. In fact, Kareo began as a 
software solution for billing companies.  As a medical biller, your day is filled with much more than submitting claims to insurance companies. It includes revenue management activities, claim submissions and review, coding, insurance verifications, payment processing, regular communications with your practices, reporting, and so much more.

column4: Once you sign up with Kareo, a dedicated CSC will contact you within 24 hours to welcome you and assist with account set up. Your CSC will help coordinate your entire onboarding timeline, which includes initial account setup, enrollments, claims processing, and ERA receipt. Additionally, our Kareo Training Specialists will help guide you through available e-learning options.

column4: You can begin sending electronic claims to all commercial insurance companies, such as Aetna, Cigna, United Healthcare, and many others, within 48 hours of signing up for Kareo. A few payers, such as Medicare, Medicaid, Blue Cross/Blue Shield, may require authorization of an enrollment form before you can submit electronic claims. Once these payers process your enrollment form, typically within 5-30 days, you can then send electronic claims to these payers through Kareo.

We also support major national insurers, such as Aetna, Cigna, Humana, and United Healthcare, as well as local IPAs and smaller insurers.

column4: Subscription fees are billed a month in advance of service, except for the first month when you are billed a prorated fee based on the number of days you had access to Kareo on the following month’s invoice. We accept payment by direct debit to your checking account or by Visa, MasterCard, Discover, or American Express. Payments are due on the tenth day of each month.

column4: . The payments are processed through a merchant account, deposited directly into your bank account, and posted to Kareo. There are no set up or monthly fees, no contracts, and you can cancel anytime. It allows you to accept all forms of card types, including FSA, HSA, Visa, MasterCard, Discover, and American Express. The rate per transaction is 2.75% + $0.30.

column4: We currently support professional claim formats, used for provider charges, using the CMS 1500 paper claim format and ANSI 837p electronic claim format. We also support institutional claim formats, both UB-04 and 837I, for Ambulatory Surgical Centers (ASC), Comprehensive Outpatient Rehabilitation Facility (CORF), and Outpatient Rehabilitation Facility (ORF).

column4: Yes. If you are not completely satisfied, you can export your data at any time at no additional charge. You can save a copy of your data to your local computer in standard file formats, such as Comma–Separated Value (.CSV) or Microsoft Excel (.XLS). This provides you with the flexibility to store a backup copy of your data on your own computer or take your data with you if you ever decide to cancel your subscription to Kareo.

column4: i cannot begin to describe how this ehr system has improved my medical practice. besides being so efficient, i am able to spend quality time with my patients instead of worrying about handwritten notes, appointment mistakes and missing documents. i highly recommend this system to any busy medical practice!

column4: spend your time treating patients, not wrestling a computer. our easy-to-use, customizable pds mdsuite practice management and electronic health records systems deliver fresh, clean, simple and highly intuitive solutions. whether you operate a standard general practice, a rare specialty or any sort of combination, our systems allow you and your staff to effortlessly capture the full range of insurance-reimbursable services and procedures, in a format tailored to your specific practice and to your distinct delivery methods. send out your billing knowing you’ll be reimbursed properly for every service. earn greater profits, invest less time managing records and business practices – and do what you dreamed of doing: giving attentive, quality care to your patients.
